description: The Cheddar Gorge is a limestone gorge in the Mendip Hills, near Somerset, England. The gorge and its many caves are the site of human activity dating back to the Upper Paleolithic.
details: Cheddar Man, the oldest complete skeleton found in Britain, dates to ca. 9,000 years ago.
